race.comment: DOMINATUS (5) looks an exciting prospect on the way up, mowing his rivals down at Northam last time out. Stepping up to the mile now looks ideal and Pike sticking as he comes to town is a good push for his chances. No doubt aiming for the 3YO features during The Pinnacles and can show his class today. MISS VEUVE (3) won impressively two back and stormed home once again at Northam last time out, finishing 0.6L off the winner. Her recent ratings stack up as she comes to town now and the 3kg claim comes in handy. Can be finishing strongly. REEL SERENITY (4) only just missed fresh and the rise in trip suits. SIR DUSKIN (1) will be better for the fresh run and he's in the mix.
